article.headline: Lipscomb 62, Winston-Salem 46
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Eddie Ard scored 19 points to lead Lipscomb to a 62-46 win Monday over cold-shooting Winston-Salem. Ard was the only player in double figures for Lipscomb (4-2). The Bisons shot 46 percent from the floor to just 33.3 percent for the visitors (1-8). Winston-Salem was led by Jamal Durham with 16 points, Brian Fisher with 15 and Darrell Wonge with 10. Reserves scored just 3 points, while Lipscomb had 17 off the bench. Winston-Salem led 21-20 at the half and was ahead by 7 early in the second half.
